This paper is primarily focused on the security of smart contracts in the Ethereum blockchain, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the development of a tool for identifying honeypots in smart contracts, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The large-scale analysis of smart contracts also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.SI).
